av_freep.apidoc:
void av_freep(void *ptr)
Brief: Free a memory block which has been allocated with a function of  av_malloc()  or  av_realloc()  family, and set the pointer pointing to it to  NULL .
Details: uint8_t *buf = av_malloc (16); 
 av_free (buf); 
 // buf now contains a dangling pointer to freed memory, and accidental 
 // dereference of buf will result in a use-after-free, which may be a 
 // security risk. 

 uint8_t *buf = av_malloc (16); 
 av_freep (&buf); 
 // buf is now NULL, and accidental dereference will only result in a 
 // NULL-pointer dereference.
ptr 


 Pointer to the pointer to the memory block which should be freed  



 *ptr = NULL  is safe and leads to no action.  

 av_free()

